</node>
<node id="&quot;ACCOUNT VALUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"FINANCIAL METRIC"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Account Value is a component in calculating Cash Surrender Value."&lt;SEP&gt;"Account Value is subtracted from Death Benefit in the COI calculation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Account value can drop to zero, but coverage remains active under the rider."&lt;SEP&gt;"Account value is added to the specified amount to determine the death benefit in Option 2."&lt;SEP&gt;"Account value is the basis for calculating the free partial withdrawal amount."&lt;SEP&gt;"Account value is the source from which total charges are deducted."&lt;SEP&gt;"Account value must be sufficient to cover monthly deductions when skipping premium payments."&lt;SEP&gt;"Insufficient account value triggers a lapse notice."&lt;SEP&gt;"The total value of the account, which must be sufficient to cover monthly deductions if premium payments are skipped."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8c5042e90fe6248acf672391208bb506&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49f6114331e9af8d645ae31de47f62d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51042d483c612bb4904ff39555059fab</data>
</node>
